subject: Move Babel to test requires
messages:
[{'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-07-22 08:21:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Works for me

Build succeeded.

- http://logs.openstack.org/14/38114/1/check/gate-requirements-install/292 : SUCCESS in 11m 45s
'}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2013-07-24 08:57:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

'}, {'account_id': 4146, 'date': '2013-08-05 22:32:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Do not merge

requirements.txt and test-requirements.txt have been merged into global-requirements.txt in this repo for two reasons.
1. This repo isn't expected to differentiate between test and runtime requirements as different projects may have different needs and use them differently.
2. Tests have been written for openstack/requirements/update.py and our CI systems expect things to be in certain places. One of those things is the test-requirements for a particular project should go in test-requirements.txt so test-requirements.txt is now used to determine which things are needed to test update.py."}, {'account_id': 4146, 'date': '2013-08-05 22:39:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Abandoned

It has been suggested that I abandon this change for the reasons I gave it a -2. Feel free to restore this change if necessary.'}]

"}]
commit_message:
Move Babel to test requires

I don't see a reason for this to be ever needed during runtime.
It is either invoked during setup.py time or during tests.

Change-Id: Ie6a0ca7a9ecb0c673cce56f2876735643ebf4fdd

commit_message:
Correct the indent level of the sample codes

The python code examples in ch_ops_customize.xml did not have
a proper indent level and the codes do not work.
Fixes bug #1203622

This commit also changes the following:
- Use <code> instead of <programlisting> for commandline examples
- Remove language="bash" attribute of <programlisting> from
  non-bash examples
- Fix a bug that "Swift only localrc" is split into two parts

Change-Id: Id49a49240d3e5e85d392d1ed24bd688e258c68f7

commit_message:
Allow dispersion tools to use keystone server with insecure certificate

The swift-dispersion-populate and swift-dispersion-report tools now
accept a --insecure option.

Also, dispersion.conf now has a keystone_api_insecure option.

Default is obviously to use the secure path.

DocImpact

Change-Id: I4000352e547d9ce5b08ade54e0c886281caff891

commit_message:
ambiguous column 'checksum' error when querying image-list(v2).

- removed ambiguity by prefixing the column with models.Image
- based on the image_get_all() method logic, changed the
filters.get(checksum) to filters.pop(checksum) to
avoid multiple addition of same criteria in the where clause.
- modified the functional db test to include this failing scenario.

Fixes bug 1205330

Change-Id: Ic2b5b9bed7c02865d66e2f92846dcc9c0e7e2f97

[{'created': '2013-07-18 16:47:34.000000000', 'message': "Enable localizable REST API responses via the Accept-Language header

Add support for doing language resolution for a request, based on the
Accept-Language HTTP header. Using the lazy gettext functionality from
oslo gettextutils, it is possible to use the resolved language to
translate an exception Messages to the user requested language and
return that translation from the API.

The patch set also allows heat exceptions to the list of trusted
exceptions that can be re-spawned across RPC calls (this is the default
behavior for all OS components) so this enables the heat-api to
re-create exceptions thrown in heat-engine along with their translatable
Message, that can then be reused and shown to the REST user.

When remote errors occur the API currently shows a trace, this
functionality is not lost in translation.

The patch set also removes individually imported _ so they won't replace
the one installed service-wide.

Implements bp user-locale-api.

Change-Id: Ib89d0bd4dd8f5240a9f3e973b8a04d0a5bfe2193

commit_message:
Small tweaks to recreation of remote errors

The patch adds heat common exceptions to the list of trusted exceptions
that can be re-spawned across RPC calls (this is the default behavior
for all OS components). The patch adds the corresponding package to the
declaration of the allowed_rpc_exception_modules as well as to the conf
sample.

Change-Id: Ib89d0bd4dd8f5240a9f3e973b8a04d0a5bfe2193

messages:

(1 inline comment)

Sadly, this patch is undoing a different bugfix, so we need to find another way to fix the issue.

The setuptools/distribute/virtualenv/pip merge shenanigans are meant to be all fixed by now.."}, {'account_id': 4190, 'date': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Donald - any comment?'}, {'account_id': 7144, 'date': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)

A fix that works for Fedora is to run 'pip install -U setuptools' after the run of 'pip install -U distribute'.  I know this seems repetitive, but it gets the job done for Fedora 19.  And, it just becomes a no-op on Ubuntu since the requirement is already satisfied.

The new setuptools won't show up in Fedora until Fedora 20."}, {'account_id': 7144, 'date': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Works for me

Thank you!'}, {'account_id': 5494, 'date': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

New patchset patch-id matches previous patchset, but whitespace content has changed.'}, {'account_id': 7144, 'date': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 7687, 'date': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

This is a pretty hairy problem with fault falling partially on the Linux distro, partially on the pip maintainers.

You want version of setuptools >=0.7 for a variety of reasons such as SSL verification for setup_requires, Wheel support, etc.

For a lot of things on the system, the system packages are going to depend on setuptools/distribute being installed by the system. The package provided by the system is probably pre 0.7.

Pip upgrades recursively (pip install -U foo will upgrade all dependencies too).

Fedora does not have a solution like Debubuntu's split of /usr and /usr/local for Python packages, so pip and yum are trying to use the same directory.

There is a bug trying to upgrade distribute to >= 0.7 (which is empty and only exists to install setuptools >= 0.7) that can happen whenever you upgrade distribute as part of a larger set of packages.

The facts come together to form a sort of perfect storm. If you leave the system package alone you don't get the newer setuptools or virtalenv. If you attempt to upgrade it with pip one of a number of issues can happen depending on which exact set of issues you happen to have happen. This is most pronounced on Fedora/RHEL/CentOS but it can also happen on Debuntu. The best solution is probably to package the updated setuptools/virtualenv/pip as OS packages and use them in place of the older ones, failing that all of the solutions have some level of broken to them and you'll generally be best off using as little system level packages as possible when it comes to Python."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'content': 'Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified

Build succeeded.

- http://logs.openstack.org/01/40001/3/gate/gate-tripleo-image-elements-pep8/2e1720d : SUCCESS in 10s
- http://logs.openstack.org/01/40001/3/gate/gate-tripleo-image-elements-python26/73f1081 : SUCCESS in 1m 05s
- http://logs.openstack.org/01/40001/3/gate/gate-tripleo-image-elements-python27/12e14ea : SUCCESS in 31s
'}]

Running just 'pip install -U distribute' can leave setuptools in a

install -U setuptools' corrects the problem and leaves you with

Change-Id: I3652e84fcfdc39065b6b86fc85b6b6602601d7e9
"}, {'created': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'message': "Handle distribute -> setuptools migration.

Running just 'pip install -U distribute' can leave setuptools in a
half migrated state on Fedora/RHEL/CentOS.  Following it up with 'pip
install -U setuptools' corrects the problem and leaves you with
distribute 0.7.3 and the latest setuptools.

Change-Id: I3652e84fcfdc39065b6b86fc85b6b6602601d7e9
"}, {'created': '2013-08-05 21:39:58.000000000', 'message': "Don't pip update distribute from os-svc-install.

distribute was updated as a virtualenv requirement, however, due to
the python distribute and setuptools merge, updating distribute can
leave the system in a broken state (on Fedora at least).  Instead use
the system's virtualenv package rather than of installing it via pip.

Change-Id: I3652e84fcfdc39065b6b86fc85b6b6602601d7e9
"}]
commit_message:
Handle distribute -> setuptools migration.

Running just 'pip install -U distribute' can leave setuptools in a
half migrated state on Fedora/RHEL/CentOS.  Following it up with 'pip
install -U setuptools' corrects the problem and leaves you with
distribute 0.7.3 and the latest setuptools.

Change-Id: I3652e84fcfdc39065b6b86fc85b6b6602601d7e9

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary metadata from the 3PAR drivers

Currently, both the HP 3PAR iSCSI and FC drivers are populating
the volume and snapshot metadata field with unnecessary data that
should actually be stored on the backend. This data should not be
accessible by the user which it is today and could be updated as well.

This patch will remove all custom 3PAR data from the metadata fields.

Change-Id: I3086be3856192a27fa1db1ada89d95c290c68df7
Fixes: bug 1203144

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-07-31 18:06:51.000000000', 'message': 'Add more locks for hosts and availability zones

This commit adds locking to all the methods in test_aggregates that
add a host to an aggregate. After adding locking to:
test_aggregate_add_host_create_server_with_az the test failure did
not go away completely. So that likely means that there is still a
contention with the host being a member of another availability zone
when the test tries to create the server. The extra locks should
ensure that the compute host is not in a different availability zone
when the test tries to create the server in the newly created
availability zone.

Change-Id: Iaf8a903d92c88c7c3092eaa00a9f7a96e6348ddc
'}, {'created': '2013-07-31 18:07:32.000000000', 'message': 'Add more locks for hosts and availability zones

This commit adds locking to all the methods in test_aggregates that
add a host to an aggregate. After adding locking to:
test_aggregate_add_host_create_server_with_az the test failure did
not go away completely. So that likely means that there is still a
contention with the host being a member of another availability zone
when the test tries to create the server. The extra locks should
ensure that the compute host is not in a different availability zone
when the test tries to create the server in the newly created
availability zone.

part of blueprint speed-up-tempest

Change-Id: Iaf8a903d92c88c7c3092eaa00a9f7a96e6348ddc
'}, {'created': '2013-08-03 01:28:13.000000000', 'message': 'Add locks for all aggregates tests with hosts

This commit adds locking to all the methods in test_aggregates that
add a host to an aggregate. Nova commit
I18ad1ac22c6aee298ccc75c978b85241ae1ac616 introduced a check that
a host being added to an aggregate is not already a member of an
availability zone. This can cause an issue with running tempest in
parallel because tests in test_aggregates uses only one host for
multiple tests. If any of these tests are run at the same time as a
test where the host is added to an availability zone it will fail.
By adding locking to all the tests with adding hosts to an aggregate
this ensures that this failure will not occur.

part of blueprint speed-up-tempest

commit_message:
Add locks for all aggregates tests with hosts

This commit adds locking to all the methods in test_aggregates that
add a host to an aggregate. Nova change
I788782a9f21ec2672551f75123753175bb268586 added a check so that
a host being added to an aggregate is not already a member of an
availability zone. This can cause an issue with running tempest in
parallel because tests in test_aggregates uses only one host for
multiple tests. If any of these tests are run at the same time as a
test where the host is added to an availability zone it will fail.
By adding locking to all the tests with adding hosts to an aggregate
this ensures that this failure will not occur.

part of blueprint speed-up-tempest

Change-Id: Iaf8a903d92c88c7c3092eaa00a9f7a96e6348ddc

commit_message:
Define behaviour for properties with None values.

Now that Ref and Fn::GetAtt might return None values, behaviour for
properties with None values needs definition.

This change will treat a None value in the following way:
- if there is a default in the schema, that value will be used
- otherwise a default is used depending on the type ('', False, 0, [] {})

Fixes bug: #1192142

Change-Id: I59ae32c1c32b1bfede7d775aa845cd14246040e1
(cherry picked from commit 15bdfe029eb9274fd37ad2d6e8ec3001ec6eaf8e)

commit_message:
Whitebox server expects deleted > 0

Whitebox servers tests expected deleted == 1.
Behaviour changed no nova side, now DB field
instances.deleted is set to the instance DB ID,
which is an interger > 0.

Fixes: lp/1208267
Change-Id: I659ab17507401f758e6ca2460b0992f3d55dda8b

When using the fake VIRT_DRIVER, we can launch an arbitrary number of
instances, the next step for performance testing is running an arbitrary
number of n-cpus. This can be done with the following settings in your localrc

 VIRT_DRIVER=fake
 NUMBER_FAKE_NOVA_COMPUTE=50

This can be used for things like measuring load from n-cpu's periodic tasks.

Change-Id: I40e0f05374e2c10c48ea6b8816ef6e7609b3dc80
"}]
commit_message:
Add support for running multiple n-cpus for performance testing

When using the fake VIRT_DRIVER, we can launch an arbitrary number of
instances, the next step for performance testing is running an arbitrary
number of n-cpus. This can be done with the following settings in your localrc

 VIRT_DRIVER=fake
 NUMBER_FAKE_NOVA_COMPUTE=50

This can be used for things like measuring load from n-cpu's periodic tasks.

Change-Id: I40e0f05374e2c10c48ea6b8816ef6e7609b3dc80

commit_message:
add oslo and infra from git to the upgrade

to make grenade work like havana master we need to bring in infra
and oslo repositories from upstream git and apply global
requirements to all the repositories.

Update functions file from devstack.

Attempt to uninstall oslo.config first, to deal with weird pip
issues where 1.1.1 is still installed, but 1.2.x from git is in
the easy repo files, and nova-manage explodes.

Change-Id: I310d40a0adc9355eea91e79598bf867ad6818b79

commit_message:
Revert "Replace part_handler.py with write-files cloudinit mechanism"

Ubuntu has 0.6 of cloudinit, and write-files doesn't work on that
distro.  Ubuntu does not intend to update cloudinit in their LTS release
to 0.7.

This reverts commit 621f5bfdbab46498b37cdc4865afa57e0f0498e0.
Fixes: Bug #1207088

Change-Id: If80863883afee28bdde6dd506826ec5710cc0308

commit_message:
Use pip -e in setup_develop

We have some complex logic in here to try to do the right things with
the requirements before doing the install of the package which still
winds up being wrong in some cases. Since having written this code,
we've learned that the logic we're trying to achieve is actually what
pip install -e does. So just use that. We have to follow up with a chown
of the resulting egg-info directory, because the sudo command will cause
it to be written by root, which prevents subsequent commands from
operating without privilege in the directory.

Change-Id: I7454f0053c36b15051b616363a5fc04c0045b57c

commit_message:
Clear new or building backups on reset-task-status

The reset-task-status management call now also clears off
any new or building backups for the instance by marking
those backups as FAILED.

Fixes Bug # 1205471

Change-Id: I478782b5e90c9965b91169a784b2ea65bda8a8b4

commit_message:
feat(wsgi): message bulk deletion

The purpose of this feature is to allow the "Location" header
returned from message posting to accept the DELETE method.

    DELETE /queues/q/messages?ids=msgid1,msgid2...

Note that if the "ids" parameter is not present, such an
operation will be denied.

Change-Id: Id8313a675c2427b772f1e9095452dda4d0d67432
Implements: blueprint message-bulk-delete
Fixes: bug #1201649

Hi Rick,

I would not expose the context to the xenapi plugins. I would rather convert the context to a dictionary of http headers, so that the plugin only have to make a simple request. The plugin is basically nothing more than:

  http_headers, url -> vdi_uuids

The less the plugin knows, the better."}, {'account_id': 475, 'date': '2013-08-05 19:05:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13: Abandoned

I think https://review.openstack.org/#/c/38646/ obviates the need for this patch.'}]

commit_message:
xenapi: Pass context to Glance plugin

Context is a more flexible object to pass to the Glance plugin since it allows
us to access roles and project_id, so it's better to pass that than to unpack
it and just pass the auth_token.

Change-Id: Ie1349682dc584486453213bfad254c307fb3ceea

commit_message:
Only call FnGetAtt if resource is in acceptable state.

This will give resource type authors some certainty on what error
checking their FnGetAtt methods will require.

Fixes bug: #1184794

Change-Id: Iec456075c14cd609cf9607f07bce23e4c6b33c0c
(cherry picked from commit c19a3deb649b6e4c5ea933e7c0ad157f4049d185
 couple of test fixups required for grizzly backport, notably the
 duplicate create from Id90edd3a09ec15d3814a322ac0b7ec75fd0be54a
 in test_loadbalancer.py is required or the test fails)

commit_message:
Skip secgroup rules invalid id tests until bug 1182384 is fixed

There are some existing reviews which try to deal with bug 1182384:

nova: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/35285/

tempest: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/29899/

There is also a mailing list discussion about this (see the link in the
bug report).

Until there is consensus on how to fix this, skip the compute tests if
neutron is available.

Change-Id: I3f0d21c23661f556354c321476ba559d4925dccd

commit_message:
Update openstack.common.config

- Add generator.py from Oslo
- Add notifier from Oslo
- Add generator bash script used by other projects to generate configuration
files
- Update openstack-common.conf file

The patch https://review.openstack.org/#/c/36493/ needs
to be merged before this one. I'll rebase this patch and
generate the heat configuration.

Fix bug #1183275

Change-Id: Id7f24874b7e3e07d06dcf14bc381b9d630f67fc8

commit_message:
Include the resource and action in ResourceFailure exceptions

An update operation performs 3 different kinds of actions on resources
(update, create and delete), and we may want to handle failures differently
depending on the action.

Change-Id: Icf60a1aea882251150a1507183cf2d23da92675f

commit_message:
Unit tests: Don't raise ResourceFailure directly

It's meant to be a wrapper around other exceptions that's invoked by
top-level resource operations; don't use it as an all-purpose exception.

Change-Id: I1e0376a4a00fc3f1114b9bc76bbb1d5d0d98b166

[{'created': '2013-08-05 13:03:59.000000000', 'message': 'Fix delay_auth_decision example values

The /etc/swift/proxy-server.conf example is broken, to enable the
feature valid values are: True, true, t, 1, on, yes, y. Thus changing
to "true". The Folsom install guide recommended turning it off, thus
using "false" instead of 0.

Change-Id: Ic10f6cdaa11f0bd5ff0957bfaf6693092c243c62
'}]
commit_message:
Fix delay_auth_decision example values

The /etc/swift/proxy-server.conf example is broken, to enable the
feature valid values are: True, true, t, 1, on, yes, y. Thus changing
to "true". The Folsom install guide recommended turning it off, thus
using "false" instead of 0.

Change-Id: Ic10f6cdaa11f0bd5ff0957bfaf6693092c243c62

commit_message:
Remove _rpc_loop and adding waiting code on execute rpc

In gating, sometimes _rpc_loop will be stopped or
delayed. In this commit, we remove _rpc_loop and
adding waiting on execution of rpc.

Fixes bug 1202865
Fixes bug 1194026
Change-Id: If0a1849bdbdefb1abb3fc5be227a6c1ede3c149a

commit_message:
Install os-apply-config in a virtualenv.

Due to the older python distribute still shipping on Fedora, Ubuntu,
and other distros, os-apply-config can not be installed with pip
install -U.  This change installs os-apply-config in a virtualenv
instead, so that it's in an isolated environment.  os-apply-config and
os-config-applier are symlinked under /usr/local/bin so that all calls
continue to work.

Change-Id: I50d7147cf74a36bbe7751d545c353ac354bdd189

Sync gettextutils from oslo

This change brings in new functionality from gettextutils
needed for supporting delayed message translation in
Ceilometer.

Partially implements bp user-locale-api

commit_message:
Various Puppet lint fixes

* Fix following warnings:
    * double quoted string containing no variables
    * indentation of => is not properly aligned
    * mode should be represented as a 4 digit octal value or symbolic mode
    * string containing only a variable
    * top-scope variable being used without an explicit namespace
    * unquoted file mode
    * variable not enclosed in {}
* Fix following errors:
    * trailing whitespace found
    * two-space soft tabs not used
* Remove quotes around class in include/require statements

Change-Id: Ia920d848e1955612a6486ec8731309e6d3a70f63

commit_message:
Replace nova client with cinder client to use volume

Now cinder support a few new features like extend volume which used in Trove.
We can't use nova client to enjoy this new feature, so we should change to use
cinder client as volume management.

implement bp implement-volume-extend

Change-Id: I4f9139bacd7d8b4c2538bff6aa54416b27c9026e

"}]
commit_message:
Rackspace: Don't raise ResourceFailure exceptions

ResourceFailure is meant to be a wrapper around other exceptions that's
invoked by top-level resource operations; don't use it as an all-purpose
exception.

Change-Id: Ie15cad32ee31beca9b0f7e9a9473ced9956a2e3b

commit_message:
db: Remove deprecated assert_unicode attribute

Remove deprecated assert_unicode sqlalchemy attribute,
removed in sqlalchemy 0.8.0. The deprecation is described
at:

http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/changelog/changelog_08.html#change-ad44af79c886d1bb283042deb64f9cbe

Fixes LP: #1208382

Change-Id: I56ad98d3702f53fe8cfa94093fea89074f7a5e90
Signed-off-by: Chuck Short <chuck.short@canonical.com>

commit_message:
xenapi: allow non rsa key injection

Currently if you attempt to inject a dsa key into a server, you are
unable to start the server because the saving of the password will
always fail. This ensures the saving of the password is only attempted
when injecting an rsa based key.

Fixes bug 1206458
Change-Id: I85e259c7d61182d32d2661662483237e7ad8feed

commit_message:
Fix Message format-string parsing

The parsing in
openstack/common/gettextutils.Message._save_dictionary_parameter
does not account for two or more format directives in direct
succession, e.g.:

%(key1)s%(key2)s

causing key/value pairs to not be copied during a mod operation.

Fixes bug 1207789

Change-Id: I56940003de3e6e2fa7dd08604d04f4c57586b0a3

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-08-04 12:32:40.000000000', 'message': "defer firewall updates to iptables data structures

One of two patches that fixes bug #1194438.

In the iptables firewall driver, each port method (update_port_filter,
prepare_port_filter, remove_port_filter) makes O(N) calls, where
N=len(firewall.ports), to IptablesManager methods that update dozens
of data structures. When the firewall methods are called in sequence,
e.g., by SecurityGroupAgentRpcMixin, the calls to IptablesManager's
methods start to add up.

This patch changes IptablesFirewallDriver to defer and coalesce calls
to IptablesManager. Now a sequence of M port method calls results in
O(N) calls to IptablesManager methods instead of O(N*M) as before.

Conflicts:
	quantum/agent/linux/iptables_firewall.py

Change-Id: If17eeaec197beae8b8aecffca1f19d4535a7226e
(cherry picked from commit e31c9fd3fed661e850fb149bf3005051e3a7c7f8)
"}]
commit_message:
defer firewall updates to iptables data structures

One of two patches that fixes bug #1194438.

In the iptables firewall driver, each port method (update_port_filter,
prepare_port_filter, remove_port_filter) makes O(N) calls, where
N=len(firewall.ports), to IptablesManager methods that update dozens
of data structures. When the firewall methods are called in sequence,
e.g., by SecurityGroupAgentRpcMixin, the calls to IptablesManager's
methods start to add up.

This patch changes IptablesFirewallDriver to defer and coalesce calls
to IptablesManager. Now a sequence of M port method calls results in
O(N) calls to IptablesManager methods instead of O(N*M) as before.

Conflicts:
	quantum/agent/linux/iptables_firewall.py

Change-Id: If17eeaec197beae8b8aecffca1f19d4535a7226e
(cherry picked from commit e31c9fd3fed661e850fb149bf3005051e3a7c7f8)

commit_message:
Fix active index's order

Message Controller's active index is not ordere correctly. Since we're
using K for sorting operation, it should be in the second position right
after the equality filters' indexes ('q'). This is necessary because
MongoDB sorts everything before applying range filters ('e', 'c.e') and
compound indexes are traversed in order. Without this patch, mongodb
would filter records and then sort them in memory w/o using the index.

Fixes bug: #1206517

Change-Id: I54ac464ce849f2dcde92a96090c27c489ea80e97

[{'created': '2013-08-04 09:38:49.000000000', 'message': 'Update mysql allowed_hosts conditional statement

In the origin ceilometer::db::mysql, if the value of $allowed_hosts
contains or equals to $host, then puppet will complain duplicate
declaration error. This patch is aim to update the allowed_hosts
conditonal statement in ceilometer::db::mysql.

There are two cases to pass $allowed_hosts to $real_allowed_hosts:

   - If $allowed_hosts is array,then remove $host from $allowed_hosts;
   - elsif $allowed_hosts is string and not equivalent to $host;

At last, if $real_allowed_hosts is not undef, then run
ceilometer::db::mysql::host_access

Fix bug 1206444

Change-Id: Ib6c33e6a27113d01326bee32c105fea4003059ce
'}]
commit_message:
Update mysql allowed_hosts conditional statement

In the origin ceilometer::db::mysql, if the value of $allowed_hosts
contains or equals to $host, then puppet will complain duplicate
declaration error. This patch is aim to update the allowed_hosts
conditonal statement in ceilometer::db::mysql.

There are two cases to pass $allowed_hosts to $real_allowed_hosts:

   - If $allowed_hosts is array,then remove $host from $allowed_hosts;
   - elsif $allowed_hosts is string and not equivalent to $host;

At last, if $real_allowed_hosts is not undef, then run
ceilometer::db::mysql::host_access

Fix bug 1206444

Change-Id: Ib6c33e6a27113d01326bee32c105fea4003059ce

commit_message:
Sort everything by K

The 'k' field is the one we're using to guarantee FIFO. Instead of
sorting by _id, which we were using for the same purpose, the message
controller should always use 'k' for that matter.

Fixes bug: #1206153

Change-Id: I74704ddb50de35e3d50c4108b28d063376a34cf8

commit_message:
Tell _list queries what index to use

This patch adds hint to all _list queries telling them to use the
'active' index. This can be overriden by the caller of _list but that,
most likely, won't be necessary. All callers of _list care about getting
active messages and provide the parameters necessary for that.

Fixes bug: #1206128

Change-Id: Ifbe48711825cadd81ebbd5dd07bc9da8a88975fa

[{'created': '2013-07-31 13:01:30.000000000', 'message': "Add repeat_actions to alarm

If a user want to be sure that they don't miss a notification it can set
repeat_actions to true in a alarm.

All actions will be called of each evaluation of the alarm instead of
each change state of the alarm.

Change-Id: Ibed79db99531a702c99a0b3746a76586d927eb06
"}, {'created': '2013-07-31 15:59:42.000000000', 'message': "Add repeat_actions to alarm

If a user want to be sure that they don't miss a notification it can set
repeat_actions to true in a alarm.

commit_message:
Add repeat_actions to alarm

If a user want to be sure that they don't miss a notification it can set
repeat_actions to true in a alarm.

All actions will be called of each evaluation of the alarm instead of
each change state of the alarm.

Change-Id: Ibed79db99531a702c99a0b3746a76586d927eb06

commit_message:
Disable deleting a chassis that contains nodes

Deleting a chassis that has nodes might cause orphaned
hardware to appear. This patch disables deleting chassis
like that by checking the number of nodes that are in the
target chassis.

Change-Id: I0c7b83457b3be17949795c5cd8292421f66fa81e

commit_message:
Enhance ceilometer statistics command with --period

Currently, if don't specify query parameter in ceilometer statistics
command, ceilometer statistics with --period will not work. This change
is trying to fix this issue.

Change-Id: I8723bad11d5c452c2834e33df9bb01ebdc6ce9ce
Fixs: bug #1202658

change search_for method to search for roles or recipes

This allows the use of application / role cookbooks when there is
no top level role to query from.

Actually, it looks like the ignore_failure snuck in for quantum-server from breaking this out.  It is not necessary in this patch, but is resolved two patches down: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/38993/8/recipes/server.rb

I can resolve here though if you like.'}, {'account_id': 7769, 'date': '2013-07-31 22:16:39.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

Sorry, I misspoke after reviewing.

What needs to happen is the notification to quantum-server when the ovs template is written needs to be removed and replaced with a notification to the agent process only.  

It appears the quantum-server even in a single server stack deployment does not care about this configuration plugin configuration file which was slightly surprising. 

I would prefer to do that in a separate patch once I've got this chain of patches merged if thats acceptable."}, {'account_id': 7769, 'date': '2013-07-31 22:25:31.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 8.'}, {'account_id': 5494, 'date': '2013-07-31 22:25:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

(1 inline comment)

Thanks for fixing the comments, it looks great! Just one more left.

About the quantum server notification: if I understand correctly the service block in openvswitch.rb is not needed and we just have to replace the template notification with a notification to metadata_agent which didn't get committed yet?
Can't we just remove the service block together with the template notifies for now and wait for the other commit? We avoid committing the useless code this way."}, {'account_id': 7769, 'date': '2013-08-02 01:12:15.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 9.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-08-02 01:59:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Works for me

- http://logs.openstack.org/70/38970/9/check/gate-cookbook-openstack-network-chef-unit/34e593c : SUCCESS in 7m 16s
'}, {'account_id': 7769, 'date': '2013-08-02 02:56:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

I promise I'm not trying out for politics by flip flopping on my assertion several times.

It appears I was incorrect in the latest comment. After experimenting today, we have noticed that not only is the ovs configuration file required by quantum-server, the process does indeed need to be restarted when the template is laid down even though the agent plugin process itself is not needed by a standalone quantum-server.

The confusion really lies in that quantum is not really organized well for a multi-server stack since the configuration files are somewhat "shared" with bits and pieces of several configs being used by different processes, even if the processes that directly "own" those config files are not running.

That said, the code as it stands for this patches context does make sense and should be correct in that 1)  We want to restart quantum-server if we lay down the ovs template, and 2) We also want to ignore the failure in the event the openvswitch recipe is directly included (by an l3-agent node for instance) with no intention of running a quantum-server.

There is an attempt to deal with the multi-server approach instead of a single stack in a more legible (I hope?) manner in subsequent patch: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/38993/'}, {'account_id': 7, 'date': '2013-08-02 19:49:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

commit_message:
Make sure the signal() reason gets converted to str

Alarms cause a dict "details" to get passed into the signal
This then gets passed into _add_event(reason) and causes
a db error as the reason coloum is a string.

Change-Id: I2ca2ad6d3b2a695598b8961d303fb808cc75531b

commit_message:
Implement failure replies in rabbit driver

Make the rabbit driver properly serialize exceptions before sending them
back in a reply and then properly re-raise them on the client side.

Also, extend the rabbit driver test to cover this case.

Change-Id: I6b3d03edcd41810125ba6442db5515754f0c1ac9

commit_message:
Add test with multiple waiting sender threads

The trickiest logic in the rabbit driver is to handle the situation
where multiple threads are waiting for a reply on the same reply queue.

This commit adds unit testing for that scenario and fixes some bugs with
it.

Change-Id: I5c8fbeec49572a4f3badbcdae414dc44dc690b6a

[{'created': '2013-08-02 06:37:24.000000000', 'message': "Fix race condition in ReplyWaiters.wake_all()

While we're iterating over the queues in ReplyWaiters.wake_all(), new
queues can be registered and we get:

  RuntimeError: dictionary changed size during iteration

Instead of using an iterator, take a snapshot list of message IDs and
operate on that.

We don't actually care about any new queues added after wake_all() is
called because the connection lock has already been dropped so one of
the other waiters must have picked it up.

We also don't need to worry about queues being removed - if we write to
a removed queue, that's not going to be a problem.

Change-Id: Ib572cbfd3a7346b76579f82b64aa85a03c1a4fb2
"}, {'created': '2013-08-02 08:39:44.000000000', 'message': "Fix race condition in ReplyWaiters.wake_all()

commit_message:
Fix race condition in ReplyWaiters.wake_all()

While we're iterating over the queues in ReplyWaiters.wake_all(), new
queues can be registered and we get:

  RuntimeError: dictionary changed size during iteration

Instead of using an iterator, take a snapshot list of message IDs and
operate on that.

We don't actually care about any new queues added after wake_all() is
called because the connection lock has already been dropped so one of
the other waiters must have picked it up.

We also don't need to worry about queues being removed - if we write to
a removed queue, that's not going to be a problem.

Change-Id: Ib572cbfd3a7346b76579f82b64aa85a03c1a4fb2

commit_message:
Sync models with migrations.

There are a lot of difference in models and actual db state
from migrations.
This patch fixes:
- wrong type of column,
- wrong length of column,
- missing indexes,
- extra indexes,
- errors.

bp: ceilometer-db-sync-models-with-migrations

Change-Id: I7f721ea604c0e1dfb8663c3acbaba66dc994e180

in pip-requires. Also, i've made some changes to djblets templates, so
it is obligatory to use forked repository in easy_install dependencies.
As an alternative, forked djblets sources can be downloaded directly
from git repository, unpacked and installed via setup.py install - all this

"}]
commit_message:
Add quick dependency fix for djblets to setup.sh.

'pip install' doesn't work for djblets package, so it cannot be given
in pip-requires. Also, i've made some changes to djblets templates, so
it is obligatory to use forked repository in easy_install dependencies.
As an alternative, forked djblets sources can be downloaded directly
from git repository, unpacked and installed via setup.py install - all this
done inside setup.sh script. It is surely not the most proper way, but
is the fastest one.

Change-Id: Ibfbb2913ce4a31911ef5415deea99e6f99926c2e

The referenced migration script uses the 'assert_unicode' keyword
argument of sqlalchemy.types.String, which had been deprecated for
a long time and was removed in release 0.8. This argument was non-
functional, so it can be safely removed from the existing migration
script to make it work correctly for both SQLAlchemy 0.7.x or 0.8.x.

Closes-Bug: #1208382

Change-Id: Ic19a24cb275748e64ce9011d1411bd803a49b400
"}]
commit_message:
Fix the migration script 203 on SQLAlchemy 0.8.x

The referenced migration script uses the 'assert_unicode' keyword
argument of sqlalchemy.types.String, which had been deprecated for
a long time and was removed in release 0.8. This argument was non-
functional, so it can be safely removed from the existing migration
script to make it work correctly for both SQLAlchemy 0.7.x or 0.8.x.

Closes-Bug: #1208382

Change-Id: Ic19a24cb275748e64ce9011d1411bd803a49b400

commit_message:
Use the new nova Instance class

Now, Nova use a Class to describe a instance, and the old dict format will be
removed in the future.

This change use the new class instead of the dict.

Fixes bug #1208370

Change-Id: I62b6b7b944c30da5758a408c08d18f7e359d7714

commit_message:
Add tests for rabbit driver wire protcol

Add two test cases:

  - send messages using the rabbit driver and check that the message
    gets sent to the expected queue in the expected format

  - send messages to a given queue in the correct format and check that
    we can happily consume them using the rabbit driver

i.e. these are tests that check that the driver sends and receives
messages according to the wire protocol.

Change-Id: I6a48085585981b17609b31f216bdca438e90e068

commit_message:
Refactor Token Providers for better version interfaces

Cleanup Token Providers to provider a cleaner interface for the
various token versions. This is included with the kwargs cleanup
to provide consistency within keystones manager/driver calls and
allow for future caching of manager/driver calls.

Change-Id: I7951d3b9d2807c5e9c5c48e8a8c49270055d0f58
blueprint: caching-layer-for-driver-calls

commit_message:
Add a new rpc call to nova scheduler for migration with target host

Add a new rpc call to nova scheduler as a place holder, it would make
someone feel comfortable when add a new nova scheduler plug-in and
want to do some resource requirement constrain validate for live
migration with target host.

The rpc call is generic enough for not only handle live migration case,
but also other cases if user want to do some resource constrain validate
for a specified host in nova scheduler.

Implements blueprint validate-targethost-live-migration

Change-Id: I54fa08fbbd703eae61710cfc4df99db35c9cbd77

[{'created': '2013-07-12 19:43:55.000000000', 'message': 'python3: Add import compatibility

Python3 reorganized the standard library and moved several functions
to different modules. Six provides a consistent interface
to them through the fake six.moves module.

However, the urlparse, urllib2, etc modules have been combined
into one module which Six does not support so do it the old
fashioned way.

Change-Id: I9a865ef1fc4de6f94cc3ccf26db0483f2bdc13df
Signed-off-by: Chuck Short <chuck.short@canonical.com>

commit_message:
python3: Import translation layer

Python3 reorganized the standard library and moved several functions
to different modules. Six provides a consistent interface
to them through the fake six.moves module.

However, the urlparse, urllib2, etc modules have been combined
into one module which Six does not support so do it the old
fashioned way.

Change-Id: I9a865ef1fc4de6f94cc3ccf26db0483f2bdc13df
Signed-off-by: Chuck Short <chuck.short@canonical.com>

commit_message:
Pop _unique_id when checking for duplicates

Drivers should not be returning messages with any driver-specific
wire format fields included. Right now, the rabbit and qpid drivers are
leaking the _unique_id field.

Avoid this simply by popping _unique_id when we're checking for dups.

Change-Id: Icbfb02ee66aebe5ef97a9a2502d8a0745e07bd8b

commit_message:
Add a transport cleanup() method

Pretty obvious that we need this.

The rabbit/qpid implementations just empty the connection pool, in the
same way their module-level cleanup() methods do now.

Change-Id: I70ba5cab3eb7a30f74cdd6cafe60087769a77b57

commit_message:
Replace cfn-hup cron job with os-collect-config

Os-collect-config is meant as a replacement for cfn-hup. The @reboot job
can go because os-collect-config will be run when the system is booted.
The periodic job is handled by os-collect-config's default behaviour of
running its command (by default, os-refresh-config) whenever any of its
metadata sources change.

Change-Id: Id768927ddfc4e7b4873fac347905e44458fd341a

commit_message:
Capture the repositories from source-repositories.

We try to expose metadata to users about what dib included in the
image and source-repositories was not doing that, so this fixes it. It
also permits easy introspection from other elements (such as an
upcoming PyPI cache layer).

Change-Id: I1e48e65f69ebe1f4556cc3bf35ccf195e99bcc76

[{'created': '2013-07-27 16:23:45.000000000', 'message': 'Fix attach interface failure to vm booted from vol

When booting an instance from a volume, image is not needed, so
attaching interface to this vm must ignore image_meta.

Change-Id: I13e52f85de11906b509b01d3472196bd7333bc7c
Fixes: bug #1205171
'}]
commit_message:
Fix attach interface failure to vm booted from vol

When booting an instance from a volume, image is not needed, so
attaching interface to this vm must ignore image_meta.

Change-Id: I13e52f85de11906b509b01d3472196bd7333bc7c
Fixes: bug #1205171

commit_message:
use 'exc_info=1' instead of import traceback

We need store traceback message in log sometime. Python logging module
already provide a argument to do that. For example, we could:

logger.error('msg', exc_info=1)
logger.debug(e, exc_info=(type_,value_,tb))
logger.exception('msg') # exception add exc_info automaticly

Change-Id: Iaf541e4f4ea139d9315ac1990f0e6079c8f8a20d

commit_message:
Fix heat hint file reading to work properly

Heat does not give us the exact API version to request, so we must infer
version 1 (/v1/) since that is what we speak. The other test cases are
all updated to use /v1/ too, so that the fakes can remain the same.

Change-Id: Ifb74546db16836aaa67fdd647aad2c5cf8aa84b4

commit_message:
Fixing crash during commit when collection failed

If a source always fails to read, but others succeeded, the ensuing
commit of all collectors results in an unhandled IOError coming from
shutil.copy.  However, commit on an uncollected source should just
be a noop, as there is nothing to commit.

Change-Id: I726c7bbaa561a3c21b61eba5e5d100b0fe324954

commit_message:
Re-execute after commands and on SIGHUP

After we have run a command and committed, re-execute ourselves. This
ensures that we will get any configurations that may have come from
underlying commands. Also re-execute if os-collect-config is sent HUP.

Change-Id: I87b4d8ce44fcbc9458a3a4fbb2445e4c9d0ad4e7

commit_message:
Set bootable flag for volume serializer

In previous code we didn't set the bootable flag in volume
serializer, and even didn't check it in test. This is the
root cause for bug #1207155

This patch fixed this issue by set the bootable flag in serializer.

Fixed bug #1207155

Change-Id: I0219785aa7f30036747c230800447e99c383042c

commit_message:
Make check for period at end of title configurable

There does not appear to be strong consensus for or against this, so
hacking should not enforce it. If an individual project wishes to
enforce this they can do it by setting 'enforce_title_period=true' in
'hacking:commit_message' section in tox.ini file.

Change-Id: I746cac906c7499f3bd77a47ebfbadab1d06a3a10

[{'created': '2013-08-01 17:18:53.000000000', 'message': 'Make Volumes work with the default AvailabilityZone

The most common way to specify an AvailabiltyZone for a volume is to grab
it from the Instance it is going to be attached to:

    "AvailabilityZone" : {"Fn::GetAtt": ["WikiDatabase",
                                         "AvailabilityZone"]},

But the first unit tests to check the value passed to Cinder for the AZ,
introduced in 134b11ccd145f982b7173bc9a5d0f1bc3e8eef8c, just forced the
value instead of obtaining it from the Instance.

Add a unit test to check the common case, and fix the resulting error (an
empty string is returned instead of None).

Fixes bug #1207416

Change-Id: I83ea2f3f0c417eb9e97abdf27a9eaffd441cb070
'}]
commit_message:
Make Volumes work with the default AvailabilityZone

The most common way to specify an AvailabiltyZone for a volume is to grab
it from the Instance it is going to be attached to:

    "AvailabilityZone" : {"Fn::GetAtt": ["WikiDatabase",
                                         "AvailabilityZone"]},

But the first unit tests to check the value passed to Cinder for the AZ,
introduced in 134b11ccd145f982b7173bc9a5d0f1bc3e8eef8c, just forced the
value instead of obtaining it from the Instance.

Add a unit test to check the common case, and fix the resulting error (an
empty string is returned instead of None).

Fixes bug #1207416

Change-Id: I83ea2f3f0c417eb9e97abdf27a9eaffd441cb070

Add support for doing language resolution for a request, based on the
Accept-Language HTTP header. Using the lazy gettext functionality, from
oslo gettextutils, it is possible to use the resolved language to
translate exception messages to the user requested language and
return that translation from the API.

The patch removes individually imported _() so they don't replace the
one installed service-wide.

with the same kwargs with which it was originally created, so that we

"}]
commit_message:
Enable localizable REST API responses via the Accept-Language header

Add support for doing language resolution for a request, based on the
Accept-Language HTTP header. Using the lazy gettext functionality, from
oslo gettextutils, it is possible to use the resolved language to
translate exception messages to the user requested language and
return that translation from the API.

The patch removes individually imported _() so they don't replace the
one installed service-wide.

Also, it adds the ability to fully re-create a remote error
with the same kwargs with which it was originally created, so that we
can translate it and show it to the user.

Partially implements bp user-locale-api.

Change-Id: I63edc8463836bfff257daa8a2c66ed5d3a444254

commit_message:
Sync gettextutils from oslo

The oslo changes necessary for delayed translation were refactored in
oslo. This patch set brings in the refactored changes, implemented
under the same change-id mentioned below.

Partially implements bp user-locale-api

[{'created': '2013-06-27 00:58:04.000000000', 'message': 'PCI passthrough DB Layer

Add new table to store information about available pci device on host.
It is important to have store such infromation because we should have
store information about status (available or in use).

Change db.compute_node_get_all() method
It should return joined PCIDevices to be able to filter
hosts by available devices

Change db.compute_node_delete() method
This method should delete all PciDevices on this node

Change db.instance_destroy() method
It should release PCIDevice.

Why release is so strange and we have 3 statuses
(in_use, available, to_delete)

It is caused by way of syncing infromation about
available devices. It will be discussed in pci utils patch set.

Add minimal set of functions to cover all cases:

pci_device_destroy_all_on_host() and pci_device_create()
  Are used in sync process

pci_lables_get_all()
  Probably will be used in future for admin purpose

pci_device_get_all_by_host()
  Is used in tests, and also could be used in cli

pci_device_attach_to_instance_by_labels()
  Is the main method that allows as to attach to instance all devices
  that are required (by labels).
  It is called on scheduled compute node in compute.manager

Add tests for all this stuff

blueprint pci-passthrough-base

Change-Id: I415b6a1dc23485bc4ef9a6f674fefca566c2e0b1

commit_message:
PCI passthrough DB Layer

Add new table to store information about available pci device on host.
It is important to have store such infromation because we should have
store information about status (available or in use).

Change db.compute_node_get_all() method
It should return joined PCIDevices to be able to filter
hosts by available devices

Change db.compute_node_delete() method
This method should delete all PciDevices on this node

Change db.instance_destroy() method
It should release PCIDevice.

Why release is so strange and we have 3 statuses
(in_use, available, to_delete)

It is caused by way of syncing infromation about
available devices. It will be discussed in pci utils patch set.

Add minimal set of functions to cover all cases:

pci_device_destroy_all_on_host() and pci_device_create()
  Are used in sync process

pci_lables_get_all()
  Probably will be used in future for admin purpose

pci_device_get_all_by_host()
  Is used in tests, and also could be used in cli

pci_device_attach_to_instance_by_labels()
  Is the main method that allows as to attach to instance all devices
  that are required (by labels).
  It is called on scheduled compute node in compute.manager

Add tests for all this stuff

blueprint pci-passthrough-base

Change-Id: I415b6a1dc23485bc4ef9a6f674fefca566c2e0b1

commit_message:
Implement Stack status and action properties

This splits the stack_status back to an action and status,
as it is represented internally in heat-engine.

It assumes there will not be an action which contains an _.

This change is needed for code (such as tempest) which assumes a
convention of all openstack client resources having a status property.

Change-Id: If00db5508bf8469b1106cac20b8fc10f7e1a854d

commit_message:
Make keeping the tools updated easy.

We currently clone a number of trees but offer no obvious way to keep
them up to date - and users are running into bugs with old, outdated
trees. Some automation may help :).

Change-Id: I2642a38aab6349d43e8b86cf94a1ac979c598077

'}, {'created': '2013-05-26 02:09:54.000000000', 'message': 'Replace setuptools_git with a smarter approach.

Implement a local egg_info command that only re-generates the
SOURCES.txt file when we need to. That is:

 - If there is no SOURCES.txt, make one
 - If we have run the sdist command, make one

Otherwise, leave well enough alone.

Also, skip doing any git processing if SKIP_GIT_FILES is specified.

This should mean that consumers of our tarballs should not get screwed
by the need to inject git processing into the sdist.

Change-Id: I163b1c153d030e79b120600a2890edeb49e1fa90

'}, {'created': '2013-05-26 02:34:22.000000000', 'message': 'Replace setuptools_git with a smarter approach.

Implement a local egg_info command that only re-generates the
SOURCES.txt file when we need to. That is:

 - If there is no SOURCES.txt, make one
 - If we have run the sdist command, make one

Otherwise, leave well enough alone.

commit_message:
Replace setuptools_git with a smarter approach

Implement a local egg_info command that only re-generates the
SOURCES.txt file when we need to. That is:

 - If there is no SOURCES.txt, make one
 - If we have run the sdist command, make one

Otherwise, leave well enough alone.

Also, skip doing any git processing if SKIP_GIT_SDIST is specified.

This should mean that consumers of our tarballs should not get screwed
by the need to inject git processing into the sdist.

Change-Id: I163b1c153d030e79b120600a2890edeb49e1fa90

'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2013-07-06 16:06:52.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

This patch hide credentials in a request but does not hide token in a response. It is inconsistent. I can see a token from keystone in a response from keystone. This is the reason of -1.

The second one is just a question. Even if --debug option is specified, a password and a token are redacted. Is there any way to check them for debugging? Sometimes we need to check tokens (and password) when debugging. The credentials are output to stderr and they are not logged into log files as long as stderr is redirected or piped. I am not sure they needs to be masked, though I don't have a strong opinion."}, {'account_id': 1131, 'date': '2013-07-06 16:06:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

'}, {'account_id': 1528, 'date': '2013-07-06 16:06:52.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

Regarding the token - I think that's out of scope for this patch. It could be addressed, but that would have to be an openstack-wide effort. It's already logged all over the place in nova rpc messages, etc. It's not that bad either - since tokens normally have only a limited time to use, extracting them from old logs is not very useful. Passwords on the other hand will most likely stay the same. In short: getting rid of tokens is a huge task and I'd rather do one thing at a time - passwords are the first step.

Regarding the cli option - good idea, I'll add it."}, {'account_id': 1528, 'date': '2013-07-06 16:06:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7:

@Aaron, could you +2 if the mentioned problems were fixed, please?'}, {'account_id': 1528, 'date': '2013-07-06 16:06:52.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 7.'}, {'account_id': 1528, 'date': '2013-07-06 16:06:52.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 8.'}, {'account_id': 1528, 'date': '2013-07-06 16:06:52.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

I removed the token completely so that the intentions aren't confusing. Tokens will expire, so they're not as critical and it's not possible to take case of all of the token cases in this patch.

I decided not to add an option for the commandline utility, but instead take out the credentials stripping completely in that case. There's no point in doing that if the password is already stored in OS_PASSWORD, or visible on the command line to begin with. Only the direct library uses will be affected by log-redaction."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-07-06 16:06:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Works for me

commit_message:
Don't log the credentials by default

Even in case of DEBUG level logging credentials (especially those that
give admin level access) should not be saved into log files.

This way of handling it has the side effect that if someone uses
password "password", it will be replaced in another place too... but
password "password" or some other keyword that can be found in the
request itself was a pretty bad idea to begin with.

Shell utilities are not affected and the verbose mode will still
display the passwords to make debugging easy.

Implements: blueprint limit-credentials-logging
Change-Id: I50d0ebbfbd44c7a5b162d9334b4fdbda67e5c28d

commit_message:
Update driver version to 1.1

This patch includes bumping the driver versions for both
Fibre Channel and iSCSI to 1.1.  Included a history change
that describes the changes since 1.0.

This patch also changes the way we do clone volume.  We no
longer have to check the status of the volume clone on the 3par
as it's instantly done now since 3.1.2 MU2 firmware.

Change-Id: I541ac7f97e6d1290bac6232d6c80e8ecf3a75dda

commit_message:
Clean up some style warnings

ksh -n, weirdly enough, can be used as a rudimentary syntax and style
checker for bash. tools/integration.sh was mostly clean, but it
suggested that `` should be replaced with $(). Sure, why not.

Change-Id: I76beff1194133444284c1e8fbbd5d87db369e47f

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-07-23 23:12:50.000000000', 'message': 'Unskip the git-based tests

We operate our tests in the context of a copy of a python package now.
That means that we can no longer count on there being or not being a
.git dir in the base of the tree (which was a mistake anyway) So make
there be a git dir in the base of the python pacakge - and skip the
tests if running git wound up failing.

Change-Id: Ie7ab5a5359cdd1415ed0413daa005abf3ea03a2a
'}]
commit_message:
Unskip the git-based tests

We operate our tests in the context of a copy of a python package now.
That means that we can no longer count on there being or not being a
.git dir in the base of the tree (which was a mistake anyway) So make
there be a git dir in the base of the python pacakge - and skip the
tests if running git wound up failing.

Change-Id: Ie7ab5a5359cdd1415ed0413daa005abf3ea03a2a

commit_message:
powervm: pass on unimplemented aggregate operations

The powervm driver does not implement the add/remove/undo aggregate
operations defined in the base ComputeDriver class which can cause
issues when running Tempest with the powervm driver. This patch simply
overrides the methods in the powervm driver and does a pass like in the
libvirt driver.

Fixes bug 1206528

Change-Id: Ieac227f321339a4069b015303b6e713ab9fad7b7

Inline comment on what I believe is flawed logic.

Generally - I think this is not a good approach, and to be honest I kind of think this is a feature not a bug, the same way errored instances take up quotas. It is up to the user to explicitly delete/restart/rebuild them."}, {'account_id': 7823, 'date': '2013-07-12 09:07:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: (1 inline comment)

Hi Nikola,
  Thanks for your review first.
  I get to change only on the condition that the vm can't be recoverable, can't be rescheduled, can't be rebuild because it does not exist that the driver didn't generate it.
  
  The implemented driver doesn't allocate any resource for this error vm which just keep a data item in database, but occupied so much hardware resource and even can be seen as a running_vm from "nova hypervisor-show", which is badly in truth. I think it is severity and unacceptable for the users who cherish their resources.

  And should not count on users to delete error vm, because there are many reasons to cause a vm error, some of them do get resources from driver, and some not, users didn't know which one really occupied the resources should be deleted, and it will greatly affect the new vms to be booted due to no resources to be claimed.
  
  What do you think?'}, {'account_id': 5511, 'date': '2013-07-12 12:21:22.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

You do make a few good points - but I think updating random properties of the instance table, and then relying on them, is a not a good way to do this. 

Here is what I would do, assuming that what you say is true and instance that failed to reschedule is 'more' dead than an instance that failed for some other reasons:

* Add another state of the instance (smth like ERROR_NO_RESOURCES or similar)
* Make resource tracker ignore those

Rather than hack the instance table itself.

I would love for some other folks to comment if this makes sense - but I personally believe that any errored instance should be treated the same, and this is not a bug, and this instance can indeed be migrated to another node depending on user use-cases."}, {'account_id': 7823, 'date': '2013-07-15 03:59:09.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Nikola, thanks for your good advice, but I think I still need to clarify my point:
1. Personally I think this is a bug, because if a vm is not booted successfully and is not existing from the hypervisor's view , it is definitely not consuming any resource in reality, so when query hypervisor-show, it should not count the resource of non-exist vm, which leaking the system's resource.
More badly, if there's a number of such error and non-exist vms, the system do have much available resource but can't allocate any more is a severe bug for users.

my solution is to erase the resource allocated for the error vm which is getting error in the booting phrase and is not exist in the hypervisor, so it can't be migrated to other nodes.

2.Bases on the above analysis, if need to add a ERROR-NO-RESOURCE state instead of hacking in the table can be reviewed by you and other folks, I will use the better way to fix it.

Russell, please help to review this commit.
Many thanks."}, {'account_id': 7823, 'date': '2013-07-16 12:29:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Hi Nikola, please review the last comment I gave, hopefully that has greatly explained the bug reported and how this commit to solve it, if you still see it as not a bug, I would try other ways or find other folks to make it more clear. So after that I could focus on the change of the code, please help to review my last comment, many thanks.'}, {'account_id': 5511, 'date': '2013-07-17 13:19:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Here is how I see it: 

Nova uses a combination of quotas and oversubscription as a way to not have to worry about these things, and deal with this kind of complexity. Once instance is in ERROR state - it doesn't matter how it got there and it will be treated the same weather it 'exists' as a process or file on the host or not. It is up to the deployer to set appropriate quotas/oversubscription limits so that this remains transparent to the user.

There are things that you can do to the instance that your patch will break (rebuild being one of them for example)

I guess we have to agree to disagree :) and see what the other reviewers have to say."}, {'account_id': 7823, 'date': '2013-07-17 14:00:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Hi Nikola,
  The "quotas" is to limit how many vms or how many networks the tenants/hosts can own, which control the total number from the manager logical layer, if there's an error vm, it does occupied a quota, but it should not occupied the resource, 
  if the vm use a flavor like 5(16384 memory, 160disk), and then users want to boot another vm ,he will find there has quotas for him, while can't be allocated enough resources and in reality the host is having enough resources which is weird.
  The resources has gone in such a way, and the quotas has nothing to do to solve it, and I think the "quotas" is designed to limit tenant/project resource, which is not related with the lost resources occupied by error vm.

  More you can see the following test: users can't rebuild from a vm in error state, because the vm don't exist except db and occupied too much resource.
  [root@XH ~]# nova rebuild test_error_1 6cc22762-d684-42de-a3da-d8acd770d346
ERROR: Cannot 'rebuild' while instance is in vm_state error (HTTP 409)
  
  Thanks for your thoughts :)'}, {'account_id': 7823, 'date': '2013-07-17 15:48:58.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 7823, 'date': '2013-07-17 15:53:15.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 5494, 'date': '2013-07-17 15:53:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2013-07-29 19:36:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: Do not merge

using the shelved_offload state here is not the correct solution, as this patch has nothing to do with 'shelving'.

Furthermore, in general I don't think we should release claimed resource when a VM spawn fails.  If the VM fails to schedule sure, but if it makes it only the compute node itself, then it may be consuming some sort of resource such as a floating IP etc.

As Matt said if "it's in the nova database, so either you can try to rescue it or delete it, but I don't think hiding it from the output is helpful"'}, {'account_id': 7823, 'date': '2013-07-30 15:17:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

Hi Joe, I use a new state "ERROR_OFFLOADED" to mark vm spawn fails and not in hypervisor, but not the "shelved_ofload" in the latest patch.

If there's a vm spawns failed and it is destroyed by hypervisor under, 
but running "nova hypervisor-show id", the failed vm can be counted into the show-list with resources consumed, do you really think this is right?

Thanks for your review:) hope I explained the point I want to fix.'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2013-07-30 18:36:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

Your commit message doesn't reflect the vm_state you chose.  Also yes, I do think its the current case is the correct behavior.  At least in the general case.  If we are going to change this and add a state for an error state that doesn't consume any real resources, I would like to see how we can get in that state.

The patch as is makes a fairly major change without explaining the repercussions of the change."}, {'account_id': 7823, 'date': '2013-07-31 14:04:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

Hi Joe, sorry for not updating the commit message with the newest state.

Personally, I still think this is a great bug, for example, if customers use heat or other tools to boot a dozen of vms,
some of them are getting error due to some reasons  , then great resources have been occupied and wasted which are not realized by customers, this is unacceptable for them, resources are money.

I hope we can have some agreements on the point whether this is the correct behavior from the customer's view first. 
Then we can choose a better plan to fix it, hack in the db as it works in path set 1, or add a new error state as in patch set 8, or the third, four...

Thanks for your review again."}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2013-07-31 21:09:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

If we can guarantee that no resource is actually being used, yes the behavior should be not to Chung this.  But I am not comfortable with the level of guarantee that we can provide on that.


Also any case that will trigger this is must likely a bug itself. Either upstream or in config.'}, {'account_id': 7823, 'date': '2013-08-04 13:35:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

Hi Joe,
  Yes, you are right, I can't guarantee the resource is not being used anywhere, thanks for the comments, this commit will be abandoned."}, {'account_id': 7823, 'date': '2013-08-04 13:40:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8: Abandoned

Currently, we can't guarantee that the vm didn't consume any resource even it didn't exist on the hypervisor under.

This commit should be abandoned for there's no way to actually measure resources consumed by spawning failed vms."}]

commit_message:
Release resources claimed when vm spawns failed

This commit fix the resources lost when vm spawns failed on all
kinds of hypervisors. It only exists in db and has been destroyed
by the hypervisor under.

The reason is resources have been occupied logically before spawning
but didn't released after hypervisor destroyed the error vm which makes
resources leak meanningless.

The strategy adopted to fix it is to set its vm_state into vm_states.
SHELVED_OFFLOADED and the resource tracker will ignore it when stating
resources usage.

Fixes bug #1193226

Change-Id: I11c419a84966c799bb7550425762bc56511cd478

commit_message:
Add new persona value in the 3PAR driver

A new persona type, '12 - OpenVMS' was added to the list of valid
personas in the 3PAR drivers. This persona was introduced in the
3.1.2 MU2 firmware update on the 3PAR storage array.

DocImpact

commit_message:
Performs hard reboot if libvirt soft reboot raises libvirtError

Currently the libvirt driver will only attempt a hard reboot if a soft
reboot fails and returns False. If a libvirt exception is raised,
however, the hard reboot is not attempted. This patch wraps the soft
reboot in a try block to continue with the hard reboot attempt if a
libvirtError is raised.

Fixes bug 1202974

Change-Id: Ifaff75b33b5123cdd3293e8f263ccb4f72ae726a

commit_message:
Fix and Gate on H303 (no wildcard imports)

Wildcard imports make reading code unnecessarily confusing because they
make it harder to see where a functions comes from.  We had two types of
wildcard imports in the code. Unneeded ones in test files that are just
removed, and some that we actually want which are kept using the '#
noqa' comment to tell flake8 to skip specific checks (such as H303)
for that line.

Change-Id: Id4705011579659fd74a4aaa05ac541e9694c483e

commit_message:
Ensure install_venv works behind firewalls

There is a problem with setuptools and firewalls that prevents
setuptools from downloading setup_requires properly. The only thing
in openstack that really needs setup_requires is pbr. Once that's in,
everything else installs via pip, which does firewalls correctly. So,
just install the latest pbr into the venv and the rest should work.

Change-Id: I838559f6f308e4a0c255af7bc27cdc669c5cf5f3

commit_message:
Call get_session() only when necessary

A Session instance should be retrieved only when it's
really needed, e. g. to make a few DB queries inside a
single transaction or to pass the session to a private
DB API method, etc. At the same time, many queries are
simple and can be expressed by the means  of auxiliary
model_query() function.

Blueprint: db-session-cleanup

Change-Id: I2ddc0cda42a84fe600c04f4624db9c2933799bfc

commit_message:
Fix volume_create()/snapshot_create() DB methods

volume_create() and snapshot_create() DB API methods create
entities and return information about them by calling
_volume_get() and snapshot_get() methods. There is no need
to create a new transaction to call the corresponding 'getter'.

Unfortunately, fixing this breaks two existing tests, which rely
on the current behaviour of these DB API methods: both volume_create()
and snapshot_create() raise exceptions, nevertheless new entities are
created.

Blueprint: db-session-cleanup

Change-Id: Idecac70893ec280c149f9227f86a6959d70c15fe

commit_message:
Execute DB API methods in a single transaction

Many DB API methods do a few queries to a DB (e. g.  SELECT
and then UPDATE, or SELECT and then DELETE, etc).  By default,
a Session instance is used with autocommit=True, which means,
that each query to a DB is done in a separate transaction. This
is error-prone (as it may lead to race conditions or returning
of unexpected results) and makes rollbacks harder (if one of
transactions fail, the previous ones can not be rolled back).

This patch ensures that all DB API methods, which do a few
queries (or call private DB API methods), are executed inside
a single transaction.

Blueprint: db-session-cleanup

Change-Id: Ie6510becffdeb78048fe4a09511ab326627d3412

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-08-02 21:18:54.000000000', 'message': 'Fix Cisco Nexus plugin failures for vlan IDs 1006-4094

Fixes bug 1174593

VLAN IDs in the range 1006-4094 are considered to be in the extended
range by the Cisco Nexus 3K switch. As such, the 3K rejects any
state change configuration commands for VLANs in this range, including
"state active" and "no shutdown". The errors returned by the 3K for
these commands can be ignored, since the default states for these commands
are acceptable for the 3K.

For the 5K and 7K versions of the Nexus switch, on the other hand, the
"state active" and "no shutdown" commands are required for proper VLAN
configuration, regardless of VLAN ID.

This fix splits the configuration commands which are used to create a
VLAN on the Nexus switch into three separate configurations:
  - VLAN creation
  - state active
  - no shutdown
For the "state active" and "no shutdown" configurations, the Cisco Nexus
plugin will tolerate (ignore) errors involving invalid setting of state
for VLANs in the extended VLAN range. These specific errors can be
identified by looking for the appearance of certain signature strings
in the associated exception's message string, i.e. "Can't modify
state for extended" or "Command is allowed on VLAN".

This approach will yield a very small hit in performance, but the solution
is much less error prone than requiring customers to configure the
Cisco plugin for 3K vs. 5K vs. 7K, or perhaps even specific software
versions of the 3K, in order to inform the Cisco plugin whether
VLAN state configuration commands should be used or not.

Change-Id: I1be4966ddc6f462bca38428c4f904f8c982f318f
(cherry picked from commit fc914f66502ee066f41780e10b0e659334ffd060)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix Cisco Nexus plugin failures for vlan IDs 1006-4094

Fixes bug 1174593

VLAN IDs in the range 1006-4094 are considered to be in the extended
range by the Cisco Nexus 3K switch. As such, the 3K rejects any
state change configuration commands for VLANs in this range, including
"state active" and "no shutdown". The errors returned by the 3K for
these commands can be ignored, since the default states for these commands
are acceptable for the 3K.

For the 5K and 7K versions of the Nexus switch, on the other hand, the
"state active" and "no shutdown" commands are required for proper VLAN
configuration, regardless of VLAN ID.

This fix splits the configuration commands which are used to create a
VLAN on the Nexus switch into three separate configurations:
  - VLAN creation
  - state active
  - no shutdown
For the "state active" and "no shutdown" configurations, the Cisco Nexus
plugin will tolerate (ignore) errors involving invalid setting of state
for VLANs in the extended VLAN range. These specific errors can be
identified by looking for the appearance of certain signature strings
in the associated exception's message string, i.e. "Can't modify
state for extended" or "Command is allowed on VLAN".

This approach will yield a very small hit in performance, but the solution
is much less error prone than requiring customers to configure the
Cisco plugin for 3K vs. 5K vs. 7K, or perhaps even specific software
versions of the 3K, in order to inform the Cisco plugin whether
VLAN state configuration commands should be used or not.

Change-Id: I1be4966ddc6f462bca38428c4f904f8c982f318f
(cherry picked from commit fc914f66502ee066f41780e10b0e659334ffd060)

commit_message:
Fix HTTP response for PortNotFound during boot

If a non-existent Quantum port is passed as a network parameter during create
instance, Nova API should return an HTTP BadRequest.

Fixes bug #1195468

Change-Id: I5914fda076fdd3ff20c81984364ca725edae1a78

commit_message:
Ensure _run_shell_command always returns same type

If _run_shell_command gets no output, return an empty
string instead of None. This ensures that callers can
always treat the results as a string, and avoids the
TypeError that was preventing the ChangeLog and AUTHORS
files from being created properly in a git repository
without any commits.

Change-Id: I880210bc3ff92ece29b216a10e1d0c918f884eaf

commit_message:
Consume the OpenStack mirror by default

PyPI upstream obviously breaks all the time. Like, literally, I've spent
my whole life dealing with it this past week. In this test, we were
avoiding the OpenStack mirror so that we could be sure to be testing
that we could build the mirror when new requirements are added. However,
the only time that's a concern is on a requirements repo change.

Add an option --no-mirror that will trigger the "don't use OpenStack's
mirrors as an upstream" behavior, and we'll add that option to the
invocation on requirements changes.

Change-Id: I8d01c1fbb8a5df5aa83ffba3b6489e374abef1af

commit_message:
Fix some Instance object class usage errors

This fixes a few places where Instance methods call
directly to Instance._from_db_object() instead of
using 'self' or 'cls' so that they can properly be
subclassed.

Related to blueprint compute-api-objects

Change-Id: I8e47901bd387048211d186f180991e8f780883c4

commit_message:
Install things in setup_develop with pip -e

We have some complex logic in here to try to do the right things with
the requirements before doing the install of the package which still
winds up being wrong in some cases. Since having written this code,
we've learned that the logic we're trying to achieve is actually what
pip install -e does. So just use that. We have to follow up with a chown
of the resulting egg-info directory, because the sudo command will cause
it to be written by root, which prevents subsequent commands from
operating without privilege in the directory.
Change-Id: Iffd068c94ef84475ebb30758bcf612075d225bea

messages:
[{'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-07-29 16:40:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Works for me
