commit_message:
Update allowed_hosts conditional statement

In the origin keystone::db::mysql, if the value of $allowed_hosts
contains or equals to $host, then puppet will complain duplicate
declaration error. This patch is aim to update the allowed_hosts
conditonal statement in keystone::db::mysql.

There are two cases to pass $allowed_hosts to $real_allowed_hosts:

   - If $allowed_hosts is array,then remove $host from $allowed_hosts;
   - elsif $allowed_hosts is string and not equivalent to $host;

At last, if $real_allowed_hosts is not undef, then run
keystone::db::mysql::host_access

Fix bug 1206444

Change-Id: I8701aea9344a9151ce3d7ac8fa5792895a5aac6c

commit_message:
Make YAML template easier to read

- Use folded block for Description
- Clarify description text
- Don't use JSON-style notation for Parameters
- Join UserData script with newlines to make it more readable
- Rename nonsensical 'WikiDatabase' instance to WebServer

Change-Id: Ieb7925e3fdb0e7f65fd6f69b9e9bbcd0235587da

[{'created': '2013-06-13 03:30:26.000000000', 'message': "Drop webob from auth_token.py

This came up as a packaging problem. Now that Swift does not need
python-webob RPM, some sites install a proxy node without. Fine,
we add the proper webob dependency to the python-keystoneclient.
But then there's a mess with parallel installs, and we end patching
setup.py and diverge from upstream.

But come to think of it, isn't it a miracle that this works in
the first place? The auth_token invokes WebOb, and then lets lose
with the results inside of a server that does not have WebOb.

It seems like it may be better just stick to WSGI protocol by
small amount of hand-rolled code and drop WebOb altogether.

Note that we keep WebOb in the testing code. The fix is purely
about the stuff that runs inside a WSGI server.

Change-Id: Iba33b11e77b9910211983aa725c69d3886e1c7a7

"}, {'created': '2013-07-02 21:08:00.000000000', 'message': 'Drop webob from auth_token.py

This came up as a packaging problem in Fedora. Now that Swift does
not need python-webob RPM, some sites install a proxy node without.
We add the proper webob dependency to the python-keystoneclient.
Still, in the face of parallel installs, and we end patching
setup.py and diverge from upstream, and we do not like it.

It may be better just stick to WSGI protocol by small amount of
hand-rolled code and drop WebOb altogether.

Note that we keep WebOb in the testing code. The fix is purely
about the stuff that runs inside a WSGI server. Therefore,
requirements.txt continues having no WebOb (apparently, was
forgotten before), but test-requirements.txt keeps WebOb in,
and this patch changes nothing.

Initial version of this patch produced an inexplicable drop in
testing coverage and Chmouel put his foot down on it. We were
unable to figure out why the drop happened. Most likely coverage
simply lied about the previous percentages and getting rid of
import webob permitted it a better analysis. So, we add some
unrelated tests to bump coverage percentages up.

Change-Id: Iba33b11e77b9910211983aa725c69d3886e1c7a7

commit_message:
Drop webob from auth_token.py

This came up as a packaging problem in Fedora. Now that Swift does
not need python-webob RPM, some sites install a proxy node without.
We add the proper webob dependency to the python-keystoneclient.
Still, in the face of parallel installs, and we end patching
setup.py and diverge from upstream, and we do not like it.

It may be better just stick to WSGI protocol by small amount of
hand-rolled code and drop WebOb altogether.

Note that we keep WebOb in the testing code. The fix is purely
about the stuff that runs inside a WSGI server. Therefore,
requirements.txt continues having no WebOb (apparently, was
forgotten before), but test-requirements.txt keeps WebOb in,
and this patch changes nothing.

Initial version of this patch produced an inexplicable drop in
testing coverage and Chmouel put his foot down on it. We were
unable to figure out why the drop happened. Most likely coverage
simply lied about the previous percentages and getting rid of
import webob permitted it a better analysis. So, we add some
unrelated tests to bump coverage percentages up.

Of course we add a targeted test for the new code too. For that
one to work, we change how set_middleware() treats its fake_http
argument.

This version also adds comments rather than docstrings, because
they need to source as context.

Change-Id: Iba33b11e77b9910211983aa725c69d3886e1c7a7

commit_message:
Update allowed_hosts conditional statement

In the origin cinder::db::mysql, if the value of $allowed_hosts
contains or equals to $host, then puppet will complain duplicate
declaration error. This patch is aim to update the allowed_hosts
conditonal statement in cinder::db::mysql.

There are two cases to pass $allowed_hosts to $real_allowed_hosts:

   - If $allowed_hosts is array,then remove $host from $allowed_hosts;
   - elsif $allowed_hosts is string and not equivalent to $host;

At last, if $real_allowed_hosts is not undef, then run
cinder::db::mysql::host_access

Fix bug 1206444
Change-Id: I7eb9d883c1617d9913899f32ef47a892c1d9a1a2

commit_message:
Add nova::scheduler::filter for managing scheduler.filter

This patch is aim to add a new class to manage the filter
params in nova.scheduler.The most useable params are the
resource allocation ratio options.

Fix bug #1201062

Change-Id: Iab2c76fdd07768471f6bab61aaf8c7eff6445a22

commit_message:
xenapi: Configurable download handler

We already have a configurable upload handler for images. Now that downloads
use the same adapter-pattern, we should provide a similar configuration to
allows operators to select their default.

Change-Id: I7d4ad7bde7e371f7d25018ae65ef4fcbd77e19a7

commit_message:
Adds root_helper parameter for DHCP Agent

Implements a workaround to address the following DHCP Agent bug:
   https://bugs.launchpad.net/quantum/+bug/1182616

Adds the root_helper parameter with the default setting of:
'sudo quantum-rootwrap /etc/quantum/rootwrap.conf'

Change-Id: If74c22c642c9f3d553901bf545fabc05f24520fe

commit_message:
Add support for vmdk files as glance images

* Adds support for vmdk files as glance images in upload_image function
* Set default image url to use for vsphere driver in stackrc
* Now using a more stable url

Change-Id: If6d45bc8dfd3c812ded5e1bcf69ad7ebd9b64f34

[{'created': '2013-08-01 06:24:01.000000000', 'message': 'Update quantum-server init script to point to proper config for linuxbridge plugin

Ubuntu packaging does not update plugin config path in /etc/default/quantum-server automatically.
As a result, quantum-server comes with wrong plugin config file for the plugins other than openvswitch.

Change-Id: I1cc9cb28a8412d33bf7ddb41ff84bb99cd28bff4
'}]
commit_message:
Update quantum-server init script to point to proper config for linuxbridge plugin

Ubuntu packaging does not update plugin config path in /etc/default/quantum-server automatically.
As a result, quantum-server comes with wrong plugin config file for the plugins other than openvswitch.

Change-Id: I1cc9cb28a8412d33bf7ddb41ff84bb99cd28bff4

This makes OS-jenkins run our tests in Python 3.3 mode in addition to
Python 2.6 and Python 2.7.

Rationale: keep our Python 3 compatibility high

Change-Id: Ia4c2964f7cc2a8e5ec0b47818698a96ec93fc892

commit_message:
Update OpenVZ driver image

11.10 simply does not exist, so this simply does not work. However,
devstack-gate tries to pre-cache all images referenced, so even
though we're not doing anything with this, it's breaking devstack-gate.

Change-Id: I64b03ed387f5205a885427498e8cf8c2a5b32b91

commit_message:
Update OpenVZ driver image

11.10 simply does not exist, so this simply does not work. However,
devstack-gate tries to pre-cache all images referenced, so even
though we're not doing anything with this, it's breaking devstack-gate.

Change-Id: I64b03ed387f5205a885427498e8cf8c2a5b32b91

commit_message:
xenapi: Reduce code duplication in vmops

A code fragment that creates kernel and ramdisk appeared in several
locations in vmops. This eliminates that duplication by wrapping it in
a new _create_kernel_and_ramdisk() method.

Fixes bug 1207474

Change-Id: Id317477cb278aa1b6d038516e202aff1bd6129a6

commit_message:
Include queue ID in unclaim to trigger use of index

This patch modifies the MongoDB driver's unclaim() method
for messages so that it includes the queue ID in the
query to the database. This should allow the query
to use an index for the operation.

Change-Id: I6ae5a2f03fafd7f617d4766f3ae08fd822c887ff
Implements: blueprint api-perf-tuning
Fixes: bug #1205388

commit_message:
Thorough edit of installation chapter.

1.Moved all procedures into <orderedlist> tags. Corrected grammatical errors. Added descriptive tags (e.g. <filename>). Made chapter titles consistent. Updated from quantum to neutron (to deal with upstream changes already made).

2.Corrected passive -> active. Moved all <orderedlist> tags into <procedure> (per new conventions). Removed all 'refer to's. Moved all links into xrefs.

Change-Id: I9d3536bc2bef422e835fe069fd1034f6aa318d91

The test_neutron_dhcp_agent_list_hosting_net test assumes the name of
the network hosted by the dhcp agent is 'private' which may not be the
case depending on the openstack installation. This patch changes the
test case to use the existing option 'fixed_network_name' which already
defaults to 'private'.

Fixes bug 1206694

Change-Id: I2c5ad2ff050f672a113643acbfe76c9360c3da8f
"}]
commit_message:
Make test_neutron_dhcp_agent_list_hosting_net use net name from conf

The test_neutron_dhcp_agent_list_hosting_net test assumes the name of
the network hosted by the dhcp agent is 'private' which may not be the
case depending on the openstack installation. This patch changes the
test case to use the existing option 'fixed_network_name' which already
defaults to 'private'.

Fixes bug 1206694

Change-Id: I2c5ad2ff050f672a113643acbfe76c9360c3da8f

(1 inline comment)

This looks like a nice refactor, but I think it might be over-simplified by pulling the teensy bit of filter-specific code up into the manager in a way that violates the driver abstraction.

I think someone more familiar with the scheduler probably needs to chime in here."}, {'account_id': 5441, 'date': '2013-06-25 21:12:45.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 6: (1 inline comment)

I think for retries, something needs to change for how they're handled.  It's the one place I've seen where the filter_scheduler attempts to pass on state to future calls.  So this state needs to be passed back to the caller of the scheduler, or utilities should be provided to handle things appropriately outside of the scheduler.

I've been considering the idea of moving retry attempt limits to conductor and out of the scheduler so I'm somewhat in favor of scheduler utils to update filter_properties with retry info.  But I would love to hear different opinions."}, {'account_id': 4601, 'date': '2013-06-25 22:15:33.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 7.'}, {'account_id': 4601, 'date': '2013-06-25 22:56:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

commit_message:
Moves compute.rpcapi.prep_resize call to scheduler.manager

This change removes the scheduler_prep_resize method from
the scheduler drivers and put the logic on the scheduler
manager instead.

This is part of other changes that will completely move
cold migration related tasks to conductor. Next change
will move the scheduler manager prep_resize logic to
conductor.

Partially implements bp cold-migrations-to-conductor

Change-Id: Iab6d414acfa32eeb36a2b8cf358ce5948652c49c

commit_message:
Add Midonet plugin support to devstack.

Add support for Midokura's Midonet plugin to devstack,
in lib/neutron_plugins and lib/neutron_thirdparty.

[{'created': '2013-07-31 07:17:27.000000000', 'message': "Hierarchical sphinx API documentation generation

* Adding a new pbr boolean option 'autodoc_tree_index_modules' for
  creating a package/module hierarchy oriented API documentation.
* Using the sphinx.apidoc module in order to
  generate the *.rst files and the modules.rst.
  The sphinx.apidoc.main function call expected to be more future proof,
    than the other options.

Change-Id: I145086387edf6b042368d4c16dd64948f67606b0
"}]
commit_message:
Hierarchical sphinx API documentation generation

* Adding a new pbr boolean option 'autodoc_tree_index_modules' for
  creating a package/module hierarchy oriented API documentation.
* Using the sphinx.apidoc module in order to
  generate the *.rst files and the modules.rst.
  The sphinx.apidoc.main function call expected to be more future proof,
    than the other options.

Change-Id: I145086387edf6b042368d4c16dd64948f67606b0

commit_message:
Only delete nodes when they are idle.

* myjenkins.py: Add a safe delete method that checks if a node is idle
before deleting it. There is a race between checking if the node is idle
and actually deleting it but having the check should help regardless.

* devstack-vm-check.py: Use the safe delete method. If safe delete could
not be performed disable the node so that the running job will be the
last job allowing the deletion to happen later.

* devstack-vm-reap.py: Use the safe delete method. If safe delete could
not be performed disable the node so that the running job will be the
last job allowing the deletion to happen later.

Change-Id: Ib302b81d142e872325bd04f2cd3e73eade9c7c70

commit_message:
Add error checking around host service checking

If the host provided doesn't exist in the table, nova-manage will spit a
traceback out, which isn't very friendly. This patch copies the same
code used in other nova-manage commands to wrap the offending call.

Change-Id: I606b22f0cea523809fcfa34f5b61ce70ba8d6152

(1 inline comment)

I don't like the changing of the element order in XML results.

There's code in the tests here like "dom.childNodes[0].childNodes[0].childNodes[0].childNodes[0].data", and I would be willing to bet there's customers out there with code that is *at least* that brittle. Heck, there's probably people out there parsing their XML responses with Perl regexes, and this'll break* their stuff.

I suggested a change inline; when I tried that, the responses were byte-for-byte identical with the exception of the type declaration (or whatever it's called; the <?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?> thing) switching from double to single quotes, and that output change is so tiny it's well into I-don't-give-a-crap territory for me.

* well, break it more, anyway'}, {'account_id': 2828, 'date': '2013-07-29 23:38:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

But I'm going to make it slightly more complex because my ulterior motive involves adding more childrens to a record."}, {'account_id': 2828, 'date': '2013-07-30 00:05:58.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 2622, 'date': '2013-07-30 00:49:55.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

I mean, the code is fairly ugly, but that's the fault of Python's XML libs. I mean, really, you have to instantiate a SubElement but you don't assign it to anything, and the SubElement weasels its way into the provided Element? Gah. some container serialization cleanup

Have json and xml use common record cleanup code.
Do a somewhat better job of parsing extensions from content-types.
Use a real XML serializer.

commit_message:
Modify User Attributes - name, host and password

At present, when a Cloud Database user creates a username, password and hostname for a database user,
he does not have the ability to modify these user attributes.
This API enables the Cloud DB user to modify one or more of these user attributes (username,hostname,password).

Implements: Blueprint modify-userattributes

Change-Id: I253cacf998e93b3d6136905dbb4a3516272efb0e

commit_message:
LVM / Block Device Drivers: Fix duplicated flags

- Import in lvm driver the duplicated flags from block_device driver.
- Register volume_opts in block_device drivers

Fix bug #1206944

Change-Id: Icb2c9411be060065ecf5efed293bacd6b735e299

commit_message:
Don't rely on prog.Name for paste app

Relying on the name of the program breaks packagers who need to move
glance executables around to other locations on the file system.

Fixes bug 1194987

Change-Id: I7721c5181b17b1f34adc279c055dfff5d17b57e5

commit_message:
Remove unused migration_* methods from db api.

There is migration_* group of methods in cinder
db api. These methods not used by cinder, they
inherited from nova code.

Add migration script for drop unused 'migrations'
table.

blueprint db-cleanup

Change-Id: I4a352fd9acb28bb86072884438af454c86559e71

commit_message:
Fix lbaas db migration

Currently the migration is skipped in all cases.
Added * to run migration for all plugins until we have
proper handling for service plugins in migration framework

Fixes bug 1183705
Also fixes bug 1205250

Change-Id: Ib019408b8822e3e128c7c271b92875b542413fcf

commit_message:
Disable logging to the stderr

The oslo logger logs to the stderr by default.
This configuration change will disable the stderr logging.

Fixing Bug 1207066

So that part hasn't changed, but 'default_project_id' is an optional attribute of a user. commit_message:
Correct response examples to match existing code

A number of the example responses did not match the existing code, where
either a collections or entity name is always included.

Fixes bug 1191794

Change-Id: I02df13d59082bcf5bdbe11dafccf09e69f7cda86

- test_delete_partition test tried to connect directly on 127.0.0.1
  which would fail on non Linux and we should have faked that.
- Fixes bug 1203907

Change-Id: I2622223c9fe5a3db2a113b6cd8d028a5db0915a7
'}, {'created': '2013-07-31 08:07:42.000000000', 'message': 'Fake http_connect in test_replicator test

- mock http_connect in replicator.test_delete_partition test to not
  connect directly on 127.0.0.1 (which is not always avail on non
  linuxies).
- Fixes bug 1203907

Change-Id: I2622223c9fe5a3db2a113b6cd8d028a5db0915a7
'}]
commit_message:
Fake http_connect in test_replicator test

- mock http_connect in replicator.test_delete_partition test to not
  connect directly on 127.0.0.1 (which is not always avail on non
  linuxies).
- Fixes bug 1203907

Change-Id: I2622223c9fe5a3db2a113b6cd8d028a5db0915a7

commit_message:
Add signing dir

Currently, my swift installation fails with the following
error message:

  [Errno 13] Permission denied: '/root/keystone-signing

and the proxy server can never service requests.

This is b/c by default the client side directory for
pki-signing seems to use $HOME. This commits sets the
directory to be /var/cache/swift/ and resolves my
swift-proxy issues.

Change-Id: Ice904a9d53432ba1a1ae9516cd0ee6204ade63bb

commit_message:
give value [] if disallowed_metadata_keys is None

The default value of DiskFile.disallowed_metadata_keys is None. And it
will be iter in following codes even if it didn't get a new value. So
it is necessary to give Diskfile.disallowed_metadata_keys an empty list
in __init__ if the default value None is used.

fixes bug #1206740

Change-Id: I8454eba47b2c691166924356ab33b0235a800951

commit_message:
Add a new break on error

A user running di-b several times while developing an element may not
want to drop to a shell in all cases but may only want to do so if one
of their in target hooks failed.

This patch gives them the ability to do so, If break=after-error is set
then a user will be provided a in target shell taking over from where the
last failed command left off.

Change-Id: Ia2f7ac4c21b64b971f87f4ae9cb867981b13eb5e

[{'created': '2013-07-31 19:10:07.000000000', 'message': 'Remove hardcoded localhost for mysql host param

Currently we have hardcoded the mysql database host to be localhost.
This should not be necessary if mysql is configured correctly. As
decisions about database configuration are outside the scope of this
cookbook, removing the hardcoded value.

Change-Id: I13a4ed271229793e634858fc2a41502e11f2fac5
'}]
commit_message:
Remove hardcoded localhost for mysql host param

Currently we have hardcoded the mysql database host to be localhost.
This should not be necessary if mysql is configured correctly. As
decisions about database configuration are outside the scope of this
cookbook, removing the hardcoded value.

Change-Id: I13a4ed271229793e634858fc2a41502e11f2fac5

commit_message:
Add argument to stop stress test on first error

If a single stress test action fails it is often useful to stop the
processing completely since all other action would fail too.

Change-Id: Iaab9b508cb243a69d70d3101c01ae53c01612d2c

commit_message:
Use cached nwinfo for secgroup rules

This stops a potential DOS with source security groups by using the
db cached version of the network info instead of calling out to
the network api multiple times.

Fixes bug 1184041

Change-Id: Id5f24ecf0e8cce60c27a9aecbc6e606c4c44d6b6

[{'created': '2013-07-29 23:17:04.000000000', 'message': "Use keystone.wsgi.Request for RequestClass

Keystone defines a custom Request class that's used in many
places (middleware, etc.). BaseApplication says that subclasses
should typically set Request as the custom RequestClass,
but for some reason it's not used in keystone.wsgi.Application.

This doesn't cause any problems at this point because Keystone's
custom Request is the same as webob.Request. bp user-locale-api
requires the custom Request to implement calculating the requested
locale, and if Application doesn't set this custom RequestClass then
most requests don't using the custom Request.

Part of changes for bp user-locale-api

Change-Id: If20ee9000aba89a5a2c94ed8a3dda7382142038e
"}]
commit_message:
Use keystone.wsgi.Request for RequestClass

Keystone defines a custom Request class that's used in many
places (middleware, etc.). BaseApplication says that subclasses
should typically set Request as the custom RequestClass,
but for some reason it's not used in keystone.wsgi.Application.

This doesn't cause any problems at this point because Keystone's
custom Request is the same as webob.Request. bp user-locale-api
requires the custom Request to implement calculating the requested
locale, and if Application doesn't set this custom RequestClass then
most requests don't using the custom Request.

Part of changes for bp user-locale-api

Change-Id: If20ee9000aba89a5a2c94ed8a3dda7382142038e

commit_message:
Remove generic exception catching for admin_actions API v3

* Remove generic exception catching
* Add exceptions InstanceNotFound, InstanceIsLocked, FlavorNotFound,
CannotResizeToSameFlavor, TooManyInstances catching
* Add decorator extensions.expected_errors

Partially implements bp v3-api-extension-versioning

Change-Id: I4e1d15a080e904e83e930fe15060b60c488a2f1f

commit_message:
update jsonschema requirements to match reality

all our tools work fine with jsonschema 2.0, as we run it in the
gate today (and for months) due to the global requirements race.
The real glance requirement is really >= 1.3.0. The !=1.4.0
remains because of a misrelease by the jsconschema of 2.0 as
1.4.0... poorly.

Change-Id: I88ccf6dca223c825ef98eed50e2270694d05955c

commit_message:
make sqla requirements safe for nova

Nova (specifically nova migrations) really don't function with
the versions of sqla in requirements. Bump these to the Nova
minimums.

Change-Id: Icaa4cb74576d301e28b23831a8ce7c1511ba8cae

commit_message:
Added check for datastore state before selection

The driver only checked for the datastore type. The datastore could
be in an inaccessible state. In such cases creating an instance to
such datastore will fail. The fix to filter out inaccessible data-
stores.

The datastores have a property called accessible. The fix is to use
this property to filter out inaccessible datastores.

fix bug #1194078

Change-Id: Id1c6b6a1bab7c9b299be823e1c0e1cbf430fb196

Re: catching the exception vendor_data_json - actually I don't think it will stack trace and exit because of the catch-all exception handling in handler.py. So the client will get a generic internal server error and a pretty generic error logged in the LOG file with a backtrace.

In general I think this sort of approach its a bit hostile to operators given its pretty easy for us to give a log a message explaining exactly what is wrong (malformed json data in file XXXX) rather than expect them to be able to interpret the backtrace and look at the code. Can still let an exception propagate up and handled as it currently is."}, {'account_id': 782, 'date': '2013-07-31 11:26:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11: (1 inline comment)

[{'created': '2013-07-19 20:38:52.000000000', 'message': "add vendor_data to the md service and config drive

There was not previously any way for a vendor to extend the metadata
service to include vendor specific or site specific information.

This adds an entry named 'vendor_data.json' to the metadata service, and also
to the rendering on config-drive.  vendor_data is intended to be a un-managed
place for cloud providers to put custom data that will then be available to the
instances.

The class used to generate the data is configurable via the flag
'vendordata_driver'.  The default class, JsonFileVendorData simply
loads data from a file that is configurable via 'vendordata_jsonfile_path'.
If that variable is not set, a empty dictionary is returned.

By setting
 vendordata_jsonfile_path = /etc/nova/vendor_data.json

The cloud provider can then expose custom data to all instances.

Change-Id: Ie2aceff1bf68edab124cd5f889aa9a8adcdc73c0

commit_message:
add vendor_data to the md service and config drive

There was not previously any way for a vendor to extend the metadata
service to include vendor specific or site specific information.

This adds an entry named 'vendor_data.json' to the metadata service, and also
to the rendering on config-drive.  vendor_data is intended to be a un-managed
place for cloud providers to put custom data that will then be available to the
instances.

The class used to generate the data is configurable via the flag
'vendordata_driver'.  The default class, JsonFileVendorData simply
loads data from a file that is configurable via 'vendordata_jsonfile_path'.
If that variable is not set, a empty dictionary is returned.

By setting
 vendordata_jsonfile_path = /etc/nova/vendor_data.json

The cloud provider can then expose custom data to all instances.

blueprint vendor-data
DocImpact

Change-Id: Ie2aceff1bf68edab124cd5f889aa9a8adcdc73c0

commit_message:
Make flavors is_public option actually work

When you create a flavor, you can set an is_public flag to be True or
False.  It is True by default.  When False, the intention is that the
flavor is only accessible by an admin, unless you use the flavor_access
API extension to grant access to specific tenants.

Unfortunately, the only place in the code where this was being enforced
was when listing flavors through the API.  It would filter out the
non-public ones for a non-admin.  Otherwise, the flavor was accessible.
You could get the details, and you could boot an instance with it, if
you figured out a valid flavor ID.

This patch adds enforcement down in the db layer.  It also fixes one
place in the API where the context wasn't passed down to enable the
enforcement to happen.

Fix bug 1194093.

master -> grizzly

commit_message:
Update nova_client.py

In nova_client.py:Client:__init__, there is already a variable
for conf: conf = cfg.CONF.service_credentials, so we can replace
all cfg.CONF.service_credentials to conf for this function

Change-Id: I74ac9cde00af00457b026fd13a43af6a2bf88ad0

commit_message:
Don't duplicate networks list on keypair import

In the Launch Instance modal, if the user clicks on the button to import
a keypair, the networks listed in the Networking tab get duplicated.

The import keypair button calls `workflow_init` which in turn calls
`generate_networklist_html` which appended the networks to the list, not
clearing it beforehand.

This makes sure both Selected Networks and Available Networks lists are
emptied before the networks are added.

Fixes bug 1170193

Change-Id: Icb750caa08673068c509af6c8df1ad57a2a30d93
Signed-off-by: Tomas Sedovic <tomas@sedovic.cz>
(cherry picked from commit 0512a12d07900430e8b399dcc27cade77d390491)

commit_message:
Code dedup in virt.libvirt.test_imagecache.test_verify_checksum_*

Moved shared image and flags values to setUp()

Moved common code to separate functions:
    -_write_file()
    -_check_body()

bp nova-tests-code-duplication

commit_message:
Move tests test_verify_checksum_* to separate class

Moved tests in virt.libvirt.test_imagecache.test_verify_checksum_*
to separate class.

Removed _intercept_log_messages() from ImageCacheManagerTestCase
and VerifyChecksumTestCase classes and turned it into a
module method.

This commit is the first step in refactoring the file.
It is followed by the commit which removes duplicated code.

bp nova-tests-code-duplication

Change-Id: Ie5bffcabb83ec2208ced343cdf75bf1197b7d5c3

commit_message:
Remove * import from xenserver plugins

Recently a change was made to how/where the '_' method is imported. This
seems to have broken most xenserver plugins. These plugins shouldn't be
doing * imports anyway so I've gone in and cleaned up all places where
"from pluginlib_nova import *" was used and replaced with "import
pluginlib_nova".

Fixes bug 1207107

Change-Id: I3b2a299cf60543e0f766becfeb4740af791b3576

commit_message:
Revert "Add requests requirement capped <1.2.1."

Fixes bug 1182271.

This reverts commit c39687edb9138c6eac675b8781a5d4bf5a51c968. The
original workaround is no longer needed, as pip is now configured to
install with the --upgrade flag and will therefore pull a new enough
python-jinja2 into the tox virtualenv even though site packages is
enabled in nova and an older distribution package of the same
library is still present on CentOS 6.4.

Change-Id: I33335314c7c1b26d630137edfa0cdc2d1947432e

commit_message:
Update nova_client.py

In nova_client.py:Client:__init__, there is already a variable
for conf: conf = cfg.CONF.service_credentials, so we can replace
all cfg.CONF.service_credentials to conf for this function

Change-Id: I27d16f631b4d801f9de7fd85cb314a58b4d047a1

commit_message:
return 429 on API rate limiting occur

Currently nova will return 413 instead of 429 on API rate limiting.
Fix it so that the V3 API will not be influenced.

fixes bug 1187676

Change-Id: I25e3f6766597c2475b4fc3203a43b159f0e99739

commit_message:
Remove sleep from service group db and mc tests

Before servicegroup.test_db_servicegroup and test_mc_servicegroup used
eventlet to put the test to sleep and waited for the service to run its
periodic _report_state instead of using timeutils and explicitly calling
_report_state.
 By switching to a timeutils fixture The following tests, are removed
from the list of top 10 lowest tests:

nova.tests.servicegroup.test_db_servicegroup.DBServiceGroupTestCase.test_DB_driver
nova.tests.servicegroup.test_mc_servicegroup.MemcachedServiceGroupTestCase.test_memcached_driver

Change-Id: I091a9975cc7e4fccb26700359d1e3b5c165034d3

commit_message:

The test .test_tilera_pdu.BareMetalPduTestCase.test_exec_pdutool had a 9
second sleep in it from tile_power_wait. Set this to 0 for testing.

commit_message:
Call alembic migrations after sqlalchemy-migrate

Removed version parameter from storage.upgrade method since it was never
used and partial upgrade is not supported by the code base

Removed downgrade call from db_sync since it's never used

Implements blueprint convert-to-alembic

Change-Id: I2aeabc111e5d3728fdcd0df45bf56f0aa68ed199

(1 inline comment)

I see one big concern about the current VPN connection model. During the review and test of API/DB, CLI and the driver, I noticed VPNConnection resource has several IPsec-specific attributes.

My question is "Can the current VPNConnection resource support other VPN tyeps other than IPsec?"

AFAIK, we have a plan to support at least SSL-VPN and MPLS-BGP based VPNs. As we discussed in the summit, while VPN connection models of SSL-VPN and IPsec are similar, there are some differences and MPLS-BGP based VPN is quite different.

IMO, if the current model of VPNConnection is specific to IPsec, it is better to rename VPNConnection to IPsecConnection or similar one.

Although it may be already discussed in VPNaaS team, I would like to clarify the future plan. The dev ML may be a better place to discuss.'}, {'account_id': 6659, 'date': '2013-07-22 13:06:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 43: No score

Very few comments inline.

I have a few more questions:
1) management of PENDING statuses. It would be great if we find an agreement across the LB, VPN, and FW extensions to handle them in the same way. Doing it differently for each extension might confuse users. Note that the approach is similar to FW but there are subtle difference, such as in the FW extension one is not allowed to update a firewall rule is an update is already in progess
2) Shared or default IKE and IPSEC policies. It would be good if one could have a 'default' object for both policies so each vpn ipsec connection would just use the defaults if the tenant can't be bothered by specifying any. commit_message:
VPN as a Service (VPNaaS) API and DataModel

implements:blueprint VPNaaS-Python-API

It provides the basic API and
DataModel for the "VPN As A
Service" feature that includes:
* VPNService
* IPsecSiteConnection
* IKEPolicy
* IPsecPolicy

Change-Id: I059d4db05118a4eecd388b8e8db0d714a8f9cb8f

commit_message:
Add security groups to the server POST request examples.

Update the server POST request examples (both JSON and XML) so that it creates
a server that belongs to the sg1 security group.

Change-Id: I4879aa817b3675fc3e5e3fb04ee696f1f0ff15b4

baremetal then we have to call it with no MACS so flavor is created.

commit_message:
Fix baremetal flavors

The baremetal flavor is now created by setup-baremetal, if doing real
baremetal then we have to call it with no MACS so flavor is created.

Also make sure the quantity of ram and disk size matches the flavor.

Change-Id: I17b4bb89f2156d4de320ec27b22143675e4dd4f1

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-07-30 17:44:42.000000000', 'message': "Rackspace database resource output is null

(This change is a small correction to my previous change
for this bug)

current implementation of rackspace database resource
_resolve_attribute method assumes that clouddatabase object's
hostname and href are set to correct values and just returns
them, but that assumption is not correct. With this change,
hostname/href is retrived if it was not set already.

Fixes Bug #1204601

Change-Id: Ia81722eb3877e15e1c472e94ed845f3425949b68
"}, {'created': '2013-07-30 19:01:40.000000000', 'message': "Rackspace database resource output is null

This change is a small correction to my previous change that was
already merged(bug #1204601). Below given code snippets show the
one line code change
(Please note the change in return statement in below code)

code before this change:
        for link in dbinstance.links:
            if link['rel'] == 'self':
                return dbinstance.links[0]['href']

code with this change:
        for link in dbinstance.links:
            if link['rel'] == 'self':
                return link['href']

Fixes Bug #1204601

Change-Id: Ia81722eb3877e15e1c472e94ed845f3425949b68
"}]
commit_message:
Rackspace database resource output is null

This change is a small correction to my previous change that was
already merged(bug #1204601). Below given code snippets show the
one line code change
(Please note the change in return statement in below code)

code before this change:
        for link in dbinstance.links:
            if link['rel'] == 'self':
                return dbinstance.links[0]['href']

code with this change:
        for link in dbinstance.links:
            if link['rel'] == 'self':
                return link['href']

Fixes Bug #1204601

Change-Id: Ia81722eb3877e15e1c472e94ed845f3425949b68

[{'created': '2013-08-01 04:45:02.000000000', 'message': 'Correct URIs in version information returned at /

The root / endpoint for Keystone returns a JSON dict
of information about the versions supported by Keystone.
This dict of information contained bad URIs, which I suspect
is preventing the v3 API from being navigated through by clients
who parse this version dictionary.

The public_endpoint and admin_endpoint configuration options
need a URI without any version path in it.

Change-Id: Ib8bf1d1f95bd86afa2a327e1cff011de8d3039f4
'}]
commit_message:
Correct URIs in version information returned at /

The root / endpoint for Keystone returns a JSON dict
of information about the versions supported by Keystone.
This dict of information contained bad URIs, which I suspect
is preventing the v3 API from being navigated through by clients
who parse this version dictionary.

The public_endpoint and admin_endpoint configuration options
need a URI without any version path in it.

Change-Id: Ib8bf1d1f95bd86afa2a327e1cff011de8d3039f4

commit_message:
Use shared token for neutron client until it is invalid

We cannot share neutron client among threads due to the
httplib2. For more, please refer to https://review.openstack.org/#/c/33499/
which reverted the shared neutron client version.

This patch stores the token once it is got, and will check the
validation of it every time it is used. Once it is invalid,
a new token will be created with username and password.

Fixes: Bug #1191159

Change-Id: I3a2124c5325a50d5404d96b40bea463a1b31f993

commit_message:
Allow creating multiple snapshots with os-multi-snapshots.

The existing os-snapshots call only creates a single snapshot, and we
can't change it in a way that breaks compatibility, so add
os-multi-snapshots that supports multiples.

The caller can either manually specify each snapshot's volume_id,
display_name, and display_description, or just pass all=True to
snapshot all volumes.

TESTS ARE FAILING.

Change-Id: I53f319340b5865ec59f14be6347219cfbfca686e
